@@TJvCheckListBox.DeleteExactString
Summary
  Deletes items that match a certain string.
Description
  DeleteExactString deletes items based on their string. It can either delete all occurences or only
  the first occurance. In addition you can specify if the matching should be case sensitive or not.

  The method returns the number of items deleted.
Parameters
  Value -         The string to be deleted.
  All -           Flag to signal if all occurences should be removed. If set to True all occurences
                  are removed from the list, otherwise only the first occurence will be removed.
  CaseSensitive - Flag to signal if the matching should be case sensitive or not. If set to True,
                  matching is case sensitive, otherwise it's not.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
